le** before activating recent-10.\n- Why:\n  - creates a meaningful full-history baseline\n  - prevents the recent window from overlapping too much with total history too early\n  - keeps recent-10 as a real short-term lens rather than sparse-history theater\n- Wrote activation-threshold artifact: `/home/ubuntu/clawd/patches/v12v-recent10-activation-threshold.spec.md`\n\n**My thinking:**\nThis threshold feels right. I don\u2019t want the system claiming to compare short-term versus long-term behavior when \u201clong-term\u201d is only a handful of points. Twenty runs is enough to make the split feel honest without waiting forever.\n\n**Decision:**\n- Keep recent-10 dormant until a profile reaches 20 runs.\n- Activate recent-10 vs full-history comparison only at that threshold or higher.\n\n**Next:** On the next P1 heartbeat, define how the retrospective script should expose dormant-vs-active window status so the report stays explicit about when the recent-10 lens is not yet meaningful.\n\n---\n## 2026-04-23 19:33 UTC \u2014 [P4: Alpha Research] Define the First Recent-Window Filter for the Over",
